{"content": "I need to multiply a4a \u00d7 291 in base 11.\n\n**Step 1: Convert a4a (base 11) to base 10**\n- a4a = 10\u00d711\u00b2 + 4\u00d711\u00b9 + 10\u00d711\u2070\n- = 10\u00d7121 + 4\u00d711 + 10\u00d71\n- = 1210 + 44 + 10\n- = 1264\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 2: Convert 291 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 291 = 2\u00d711\u00b2 + 9\u00d711\u00b9 + 1\u00d711\u2070\n- = 2\u00d7121 + 9\u00d711 + 1\u00d71\n- = 242 + 99 + 1\n- = 342\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 3: Multiply in base 10**\n- 1264 \u00d7 342 = 432,288\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 4: Convert 432,288 back to base 11**\n- 432,288 \u00f7 11 = 39,298 R 10 (a)\n- 39,298 \u00f7 11 = 3,572 R 6\n- 3,572 \u00f7 11 = 324 R 8\n- 324 \u00f7 11 = 29 R 5\n- 29 \u00f7 11 = 2 R 7\n- 2 \u00f7 11 = 0 R 2\n\nReading remainders from bottom to top: 27586a\n\n**Answer: 27586a**", "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5", "prompt_tokens": 363, "completion_tokens": 397}